Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1030
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 25-8-10.
Synopsis: Electrology services. Provides that an applicant for an
electrologist license does not need to hold a cosmetologist license or
esthetician license before applying for an electrologist license.
Requires an applicant to complete a combined total of 600 hours of
education and experience required under the rules adopted by the state
board of cosmetology and barber examiners (board) beginning July 1,
2027. Requires the board to amend the rules for electrology training in
a beauty culture school not later than June 30, 2027.
Effective: July 1, 2026; July 1, 2027.
Errington, Criswell, Pierce K
December 1, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Employment, Labor and
Pensions.
