2
1 SECTION 2. IC 25-8-10-3.1, AS ADDED BY P.L.170-2013,
2 SECTION 67, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2027]: Sec. 3.1. If a person does not receive a satisfactory
4 grade on the examination described in section 3(3) 3(2) of this chapter,
5 the person may repeat the examination without completing any
6 additional study in electrology.
7 SECTION 3. [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026] (a) Not later than June
8 30, 2027, the state board of cosmetology and barber examiners
9 shall amend:
10 (1) 820 IAC 3-1-13 to allow electrology services to be
11 performed in the same room that is used for esthetics services,
12 although not at the same time;
13 (2) 820 IAC 3-2-10 to allow esthetics services to be performed
14 in the same room that is used for electrology services,
15 although not at the same time; and
16 (3) 820 IAC 4-4-7 to require a combined total of six hundred
17 (600) hours of education and experience for electrology
18 training.
19 (b) This SECTION expires July 1, 2028.
